{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.29",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 29,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 29 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:1",
      "text": "He that sheweth mercy, lendeth to his neighbour: and he that is stronger in hand, keepeth the commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:2",
      "text": "Lend to thy neighbour in the time of his need, and pay thou thy neighbour again in due time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:3",
      "text": "Keep thy word, and deal faithfully with him: and thou shalt always find that which is necessary for thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:4",
      "text": "Many have looked upon a thing lent as a thing found, and have given trouble to them that helped them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:5",
      "text": "Till they receive, they kiss the hands of the lender, and in promises they humble their voice:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:6",
      "text": "But when they should repay, they will ask time, and will return tedious and murmuring words, and will complain of the time:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:7",
      "text": "And if he be able to pay, he will stand off, he will scarce pay one half, and will count it as if he had found it:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:8",
      "text": "But if not, he will defraud him of his money, and he shall get him for an enemy without cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:9",
      "text": "And he will pay him with reproaches and curses, and instead of honour and good turn will repay him injuries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:10",
      "text": "Many have refused to lend, not out of wickedness, but they were afraid to be defrauded without cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:11",
      "text": "But yet towards the poor be thou more hearty, and delay not to shew him mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:12",
      "text": "Help the poor because of the commandment: and send him not away empty handed because of his poverty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:13",
      "text": "Lose thy money for thy brother and thy friend: and hide it not under a stone to be lost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:14",
      "text": "Place thy treasure in the commandments of the most High, and it shall bring thee more profit than gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:15",
      "text": "Shut up alms in the heart of the poor, and it shall obtain help for thee against all evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:16",
      "text": "Better than the shield of the mighty, and better than the spear:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:17",
      "text": "It shall fight for thee against thy enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:18",
      "text": "A good man is surety for his neighbour: and he that hath lost shame, will leave him to himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:19",
      "text": "Forget not the kindness of thy surety: for he hath given his life for thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:20",
      "text": "The sinner and the unclean fleeth from his surety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:21",
      "text": "A sinner attributeth to himself the goods of his surety: and he that is of an unthankful mind will leave him that delivered him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:22",
      "text": "A man is surety for his neighbour: and when he hath lost all shame, he shall forsake him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:23",
      "text": "Evil suretyship hath undone many of good estate, and hath tossed them as a wave of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:24",
      "text": "It hath made powerful men to go from place to place round about, and they have wandered in strange countries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:25",
      "text": "A sinner that transgresseth the commandment of the Lord, shall fall into an evil suretyship: and he that undertaketh many things, shall fall into judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:26",
      "text": "Recover thy neighbour according to thy power, and take heed to thyself that thou fall not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:27",
      "text": "The chief thing for man's life is water and bread, and clothing, and a house to cover shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:28",
      "text": "Better is the poor man's fare under a roof of boards, than sumptuous cheer abroad in another man's house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:29",
      "text": "Be contented with little instead of much, and thou shalt not hear the reproach of going abroad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:30",
      "text": "It is a miserable life to go as a guest from house to house: for where a man is a stranger, he shall not deal confidently, nor open his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:31",
      "text": "He shall entertain and feed, and give drink to the unthankful, and moreover he shall hear bitter words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:32",
      "text": "Go, stranger, and furnish the table, and give others to eat what thou hast in thy hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:33",
      "text": "Give place to the honourable presence of my friends: for I want my house, my brother being to be lodged with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.29.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 29:34",
      "text": "These things are grievous to a man of understanding: the upbraiding of houseroom, and the reproaching of the lender.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
